			A dedicated user account was created for testing and programming in Linux. This test user account must not have sudo privileges, and all other user accounts should have their permissions isolated. The test user account should not have any permissions on other user accounts. This ensures that if programs encounter errors on the test account, other users' data will not be corrupted or leaked. It's crucial to double-check that the permissions are set correctly. The test user account should not use commands like ls, find, or vi to search, read, or write to other users' folders and files. Other factors may need to be considered for this mechanism, and additional information should be added as necessary.
